question.en:
Consider this scenario:
class Order {
  status: string = 'pending';
  items: OrderItem[];
  placeOrder() { this.status = 'placed'; }
  cancelOrder() { this.status = 'cancelled'; }
}
If you need to track all state transitions for audit purposes and replay order history, what pattern should replace direct state mutation?

